<PostLayout
  title="OpenClaw journal — cost and deployment thoughts"
  description="Early thoughts on cost, hosting, setup complexity, maintenance, and whether the deployment overhead is worth it."
  pubDate={new Date("2026-03-26")}
  badge="Journal"
  tags={["openclaw", "journal", "cost", "deployment"]}
>
  <p>
    One of the most practical questions around OpenClaw is whether the system is worth the cost and deployment
    overhead.
  </p>

  <p>
    That includes actual money, but also time, attention, setup friction, and maintenance burden.
  </p>

  <h2>Cost is more than price</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>setup time</li>
    <li>troubleshooting effort</li>
    <li>how much supervision the system still needs</li>
    <li>how often the workflow breaks in annoying ways</li>
    <li>whether the saved time is real or just theoretical</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The practical standard</h2>

  <p>
    If OpenClaw costs me attention faster than it returns leverage, then the deployment is not good enough yet. If it
    reliably reduces fragmentation, helps me follow through, and stays maintainable, then the complexity starts to
    justify itself.
  </p>
</PostLayout>
